other_tests.findings: Gallstones within the bladder lumen. Mural hyperenhancement and marked pericholecystic edema consistent with acute cholecystitis. Mild perfusional abnormality within the adjacent liver parenchyma. The intra and extrahepatic biliary tree are normal in caliber without evidence of biliary obstruction or choledocholithiasis. Normal T1 signal of the pancreas with no pancreatic ductal dilatation or mass. The spleen, adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. No hydronephrosis. The gastrointestinal tract is normal in caliber. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric adenopathy.
